Flask App Containerization and Docker Hub Deployment
🎯 Objective

To create a Flask application, containerize it using Docker, run it locally, and push the image to Docker Hub.

✅ Step 1 — Open Docker
Open Docker Desktop from Start menu
Wait until Docker is fully running

✔ Check: docker --version

✅ Step 2 — Open Command Prompt
Press Win + R
Type cmd
Press Enter

✅ Step 3 — Create Project Folder
mkdir flask-docker-app
cd flask-docker-app

✔ Check: dir

✅ Step 4 — Create app.py
notepad app.py

Paste:

from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Hello from Dockerised Flask!"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)

✔ Save → Close

✔ Check: dir

✅ Step 5 — Create requirements.txt
notepad requirements.txt

Paste:

flask

✔ Save → Close

✅ Step 6 — Create Dockerfile
notepad Dockerfile

Paste:

FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

⚠ IMPORTANT while saving:

File name: Dockerfile
Save as type: All Files (.)

✔ Check:

dir

Must show:

app.py
requirements.txt
Dockerfile
✅ Step 7 — Build Docker Image
docker build -t flask-docker-app .

✔ Check:

docker images
✅ Step 8 — Run Container
docker run -p 5000:5000 flask-docker-app

✔ Open browser:

http://localhost:5000

✔ Output:

Hello from Dockerised Flask!
✅ Step 9 — Stop Container

Press:

Ctrl + C
✅ Step 10 — Login to Docker Hub
docker login

✔ Output:

Login Succeeded
✅ Step 11 — Tag Image
docker tag flask-docker-app santhosh1170/flask-docker-app:latest
✅ Step 12 — Push to Docker Hub
docker push santhosh1170/flask-docker-app:latest

✔ Output:
Layers pushed successfully

✅ Step 13 — Verify Output

Open:

https://hub.docker.com/r/santhosh1170/flask-docker-app

✔ Check:

Image visible
Updated time shown
✅ Expected Output
Browser shows:
Hello from Dockerised Flask!
Docker Hub shows uploaded image
🎤 Viva Explanation
Created Flask app
Created Dockerfile
Built Docker image
Ran container and verified output
Tagged and pushed image to Docker Hub
🧾 Final Statement

Flask app was successfully containerized using Docker and deployed to Docker Hub.

⚠ Important Note

Always save:

Dockerfile → Save as type = All Files (*.*)

Otherwise it becomes Dockerfile.txt and build fails.
